BT /F2 14 Tf 54 712.0 Td (CHAPTER 6: SEATING CHART SYSTEM) Tj ET
54 684.0 m 558 684.0 l 0.5 w S
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 658.2 Td (Seating Chart Strategy) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 630.4 Td (Creating a seating chart can feel overwhelming, but it ensures your guests have the best) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 616.4 Td (possible experience. People who know each other and get along will be seated together,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 602.4 Td (creating natural conversation and comfort.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 578.6 Td (Tips for successful seating arrangements:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 564.6 Td (- Start with the head table and VIP tables first) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 550.6 Td (- Group by relationship: college friends, work colleagues, family branches) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 536.6 Td (- Consider conversation compatibility \(shared interests, similar ages\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 522.6 Td (- Separate known conflicts \(divorced parents, feuding relatives\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 508.6 Td (- Place elderly or mobility-limited guests near exits and restrooms) Tj ET
